Package: partition
Title: Race to Solve the Partition Problem
Version: 0.0.1.9000
Authors@R: person("Arnaud", "Malapert", email = "arnaud.malapert@unice.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Collection of functions for a R student project. The goal is to
    select the best algorithm for solving the partition problem with racing
    methods. The partition problem consists in finding a bi-partition of a set
    of integers which minimizes the difference between their sums.
URL: https://github.com/arnaud-m/partition
BugReports: https://github.com/arnaud-m/partition/issues    
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.3)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
Suggests:
    testthat,
    R.utils,
    lpSolve
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Imports:
    race
